🔹 Definition (What is Sliding Window?)
                Sliding Window is a technique used to process a continuous part (subarray / substring)
                 of fixed or variable size without recalculating everything again.

            👉 Instead of calculating sum again and again,
            👉 We remove one element and add one element when the window moves.

Short definition:
            Sliding Window means maintaining a window of elements and sliding it forward by adding the next element and
            removing the previous one.

Explanation (With your example)
    Given:
    plates = {120, 100, 110, 90, 130}
    k = 3

Step 1: First window
        [120, 100, 110] → sum = 330

Step 2: Slide the window

        Remove left, add right 👇

        [100, 110, 90] → sum = 300
        [110, 90, 130] → sum = 330


        👉 We are not recalculating full sum
        👉 We only adjust the sum

        That is sliding window 💡

🔹 Why Sliding Window is used?
            Because problems like:

            Maximum / minimum sum

            Continuous subarray

            Fixed range problems

            can be solved faster using sliding window.

🔹 Advantages ✅
                1  Time Efficient (Fast)

                Normal way → O(n²)

                Sliding Window → O(n) 🚀

                👉 Best for large inputs

                2️⃣ No Recalculation

                Old value remove

                New value add

                👉 Less CPU work

                3️⃣ Easy to Optimize Code

                Clean logic

                Less loops

                4️⃣ Frequently Asked in Interviews

                Amazon

                Google

                Microsoft

                Flipkart

                👉 Very important DSA concept````

🔹 Disadvantages ❌
            1  Only works for continuous data

            Subarray

            Substring

            ❌ Cannot be used for random elements

            2️⃣ Not suitable for all problems

            Some problems need backtracking

            Some need DP

            3️⃣ Confusing for beginners

            i - k

            remove + add logic

            👉 First time paakumbodhu confusion varum 😅

            4️⃣ Window size dependency

            Fixed window → easy

            Variable window → little tricky

            🔹 Where Sliding Window is used? (Examples)

            Maximum sum of K elements

            Longest substring without repeating characters

            Average of subarrays

            Rainwater trapping (with variations)``

🔹 One-line summary 🧠

Sliding Window = Fast way to solve continuous range problems by moving a window instead of recalculating